.s-vgTop2.s-vgBottom2
  %div{class: @presenter.pdf_term_title}
    Salary:
    %span.js-salaryText
  This is your gross annual salary, payable in accordance with the standard payroll practices of
  the Company. Your salary, as well as all other forms of compensation referred to in this letter,
  is subject to all withholdings and payroll taxes and other deductions as required by law.


.s-vgTop2.s-vgBottom2
  %div{class: @presenter.pdf_term_title}
    Number of Options:
    %span.js-numberOfOptionsText
  These options, which are granted to you pursuant to the Company's equity incentive plan, represent
  the number of shares of Common Stock that you have the right (but not obligation) to purchase in
  the future.  Unless and to the extent limited by applicable law, each of these options shall be an
  Incentive Stock Option.  You do not and will not own any of these shares of Common Stock unless your
  exercise your options.  Unless your options have an early-exercise feature (see below), you will not
  be able to exercise options until the underlying shares have vested.  Later Equity Financings or Liquidity
  Events may change this.  See "How You Get Your ownership" and "What happens when you leave" below.


.s-vgTop2.s-vgBottom2
  %div{class: @presenter.pdf_term_title}
    Vesting Period:
    %span.js-vestingYearsText>
    ,
    %span.js-vestingCliffYearsText
    cliff
  You will not have any equity ownership or options when you start.  You will not own any shares of the Company
  until you exercise your options, and the shares underlying your options are subject to a vesting schedule.
  Unless your options have an early-exercise feature (see below), you will not be able to exercise your options
  until the underlying shares have vested.
  .js-noVestingCliff.u-hidden
    These underlying shares will not start to vest until your start date.  Thereafter, the shares will vest monthly over the remainder of the vesting period.
  .js-yesVestingCliff.u-hidden
    These underlying shares will not start to vest until you reach the cliff.  If you quit just one day before the cliff, then all of the underlying share will remain unvested and you will forfeit the ability to exercise any of your options.  At the cliff, a percentage of your shares derived by dividing the period of the cliff by the entire vesting period will vest all at once.  Your remaining unvested shares will vest monthly thereafter over the remainder of the vesting period.


.s-vgTop2.s-vgBottom2
  %div{class: @presenter.pdf_term_title}
    Loading: None
  We do not Front-Load or Back-Load your vesting.  After the cliff, the shares of the Company underlying your options will vest at the same rate at all times.  Back-Loading and Front-Loading distorts both the Company's and your decision on if or when you decide to leave.  For example, if 50% of the shares underlying your options vested in your last year, we would have a financial incentive to fire you before that last year, even if you were doing well.


.s-vgTop2.s-vgBottom2
  %div{class: @presenter.pdf_term_title}
    Early Exercise:
    %span.js-earlyExerciseText
  .js-earlyExerciseExplanation.js-yes.u-hidden
    If you choose, you can exercise all of your options early when you join.  The equity you are entitled to still vests over time, just with a different mechanism.  You take on financial risk in exchange for more favorable tax treatment if the Company does well.  If the Company undergoes a Dissolution Event, or undergoes a Liquidity Event and is acquired for less than the preference floor (see below), the money you spent to exercise your options will be a total loss.
  .js-earlyExerciseExplanation.js-no.u-hidden
    You may not exercise your options early. Your options may be exercised only in accordance with your vesting schedule.

